Title : Portal:Current events/2014 April 25
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|04|25}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]]:
**A Ukrainian military helicopter is destroyed after being hit by a [[rocket-propelled grenade]] at a base near the town of [[Kramatorsk]] in Eastern Ukraine. [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/ukraine/10787281/Ukraine-helicopter-hit-by-grenade-taking-off.html (''The Daily Telegraph'')]
*At least 25 people are killed and several injured in a series of bomb blasts targeted at [[Shi'ite]] rally in [[Baghdad]], Iraq. The attack comes less than a week before [[Iraqis]] are due to head to the polls in parliamentary [[Iraqi parliamentary election, 2014|elections]].[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-27165504 (BBC)]
*A bomb detonates in [[Karachi]], Pakistan, killing 4 people and wounding 25. [http://www.miamiherald.com/2014/04/25/4079717/bomb-kills-4-wounds-25-in-southern.html (AP via ''Miami Herald'')]
*[[Maoists]] set off a landmine on a bus carrying officials near [[Dumka]], [[Jharkhand]], India, killing 3 people and injuring another 10. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-27153670 (BBC)]

;Disasters and accidents
*A stampede ensues in [[Kikwit]], Democratic Republic of the Congo, during a tribute festival for [[King Kester Emeneya]], killing 23 people. [https://news.yahoo.com/concert-stampede-kills-23-southwest-congo-104759164.html (AP via Yahoo! News)]
*Flash floods in northern Afghanistan kill at least 80 people. [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-27157042 (BBC)]

;Elections and politics
*The [[Government of the United Kingdom|UK government]] launches an inquiry after the ''[[Liverpool Echo]]'' reported that [[Whitehall]] computers had been used to post offensive remarks about the [[Hillsborough disaster]] on [[Wikipedia]] pages relating to the topic. [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-27165844 (BBC)]

;Health and environment
*China amends its [[Environmental policy in China|environmental protection laws]] to help fight pollution and reverse [[Environmental issues in China|environmental damage]] in the country. [http://www.voanews.com/content/china-revises-environmental-law-to-address-pollution-problems/1900981.html (VOA)]

;International relations
*North Korea announces that it has detained a 24-year-old US tourist, Miller Matthew Todd, for "rash behavior" during the immigration process. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-27162992 (BBC)]

;Law and crime
*The ex-[[chief financial officer]] of [[Bank of America]], Joe Price, agrees to pay a [[American dollar|$]]7.5 million fine for misleading investors during the acquisition of [[Merrill Lynch]]. [http://www.foxbusiness.com/industries/2014/04/25/bofa-ex-cfo-agrees-to-settle-ny-lawsuit-over-merrill-wsj/ (Reuters via Fox Business)]

;Science and technology
*Scientists announce the discovery of ''[[Kryptodrakon]]'', the oldest [[pterosaur]] yet found.[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Home/Science/Ancestor-of-giant-flying-reptiles-found-in-China/articleshow/34212208.cms (''Times of India'')]

;Business
*Some customers executed the SAP CIF and faced issues months later

